Mexican Stocks: Alfa, Cemex, Industrias Penoles Advance

-- B y   L e o n   L a z a r o f f
-- 
2011-09-26T21:40:12Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-09-26/mexican-stocks-alfa-cemex-advance-industrias-penoles-declines.html
The following companies had unusual
price changes in  Mexico  trading. Stock symbols are in
parentheses and prices are as of 4 p.m. New York time.  The IPC index rose 2.4 percent to 33,385.94.  Alfa SAB (ALFAA MM), the world’s largest producer of
aluminum engine heads, gained 5.5 percent to 142.96 pesos amid
speculation European leaders will act to prevent the region’s
debt crisis from getting worse. Shares fell 11 percent last
week.  Cemex SAB (CEMEXCPO MM), the largest cement maker in the
Americas, advanced 4.2 percent to 5.01 pesos as shares were
raised to “overweight” from “equalweight” at  Barclays
Capital  by equity analyst Benjamin Theurer.  Industrias Penoles SAB (PE&OLES* MM), Mexico’s largest
silver producer, gained 3.3 percent to 536.88 pesos as silver
for December delivery rose as much as 2.9 percent.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Leon Lazaroff in New York at 
